    "path": "src/agent/plan",
    "name": "plan",
    "purpose": "Owns the agent-side plan hub module (renamed from the plan queue): PlanRecord stores a PlanSignature, Plan, run StepSignatures, and a remaining-step counter and now implements a manual Clone; PlanHub keeps PlanRecords in insertion order behind a mutex and routes plan events, reserving a contiguous step-number block via TaskState::step_count in run_plan and emitting StepEvent::Trigger for each step, plus insertion, lookup, listing, completion tracking, and a stringify snapshot; PlanStringify renders current plan text and pending intention text for prompts; PlanError reports duplicate plans, missing plans, and missing steps; parse_plan converts the model's flat plan output (run_steps given as { tool: { name, description, input } } objects and intent-only pending_steps) into a protocol Plan, deriving each run step's ExecutionSignature from the task.",
